Let me know.

I solved the problem by change `self.data` to `[self.data]` in loader.py :: class ROIIter :: def next, and add an if statement because the code runs normal and no error shows when it runs the RPN training phase:
```
def next(self):
    if self.iter_next():
        self.get_batch()
        self.cur += self.batch_size
        if self.mode=='train':
            return mx.io.DataBatch(data=self.data, label=self.label,
                                                  pad=self.getpad(), index=self.getindex(),
                                                  provide_data=self.provide_data, provide_label=self.provide_label)
        else:
            return mx.io.DataBatch(data=[self.data], label=[self.label],
                                                    pad=self.getpad(), index=self.getindex(),
                                                    provide_data=self.provide_data, provide_label=self.provide_label)
    else:
        raise StopIteration
```
Based on the above modification, other related lines need also be modified:
change `databatch.data` to `databatch.data[0]` in generate.py and tester.py.
The error and the modification is quite weird and I still don't know why. But it works and run through after the modification.

